Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Pop the @British chicken thighs{3} into a #bowl{} with a drizzle of oil, the @lemon & herb seasoning{} and garlic. Season with salt and pepper, stir to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Halve and peel the @echalion shallot{1}(halved and peeled), then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

When the chicken is browned, pop it onto a baking tray lined with foil. Add the shallot to the tray with a drizzle of oil.

Bake the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, stir the @fresh pesto{32%g} and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} together. Set aside.

When the chicken and shallot are cooked, toss through the @peas{120%g} and @butter{10%g}. Cover to keep warm while the potatoes finish cooking.

Share the roast potatoes between your bowls. Top with the chicken, roasted shallot and peas.

Dollop on the pesto mayo and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish.

Enjoy!